        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 7:47PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 747 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Eudora, or 11 miles west of Hernando, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southaven, Olive Branch, Hernando, Coldwater, Lake Cormorant,
Phillipp, Eudora, Independence, Lewisburg, Arkabutla, Robinsonville,
Newport, Clack, Trinity, Cockrum, Frees Corners, Cedarview, Bright,
Nesbit, and Banks.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
northwestern Mississippi.</instruction>
